===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|門|王|ls=ic|t1=gate|t2=king}}. The original meaning “intercalary” is derived from kings' ancient practice of remaining within the palace gates on a leap day (which was in excess of the lunar calendar's 364 days, whence the meanings “remainder” and “surplus”), not engaging in their usual governing functions.

